import React from 'react'
  import { MDXTag } from '@mdx-js/tag'
  import {Playground, PropsTable} from 'docz'
import Button from './Button'

export default ({components, ...props}) => <MDXTag name="wrapper"  components={components}>
<MDXTag name="h1" components={components} props={{"id":"button"}}>{`Button`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"basic-usage"}}>{`Basic usage`}</MDXTag>
<Playground __position={0} __code={`<Button>SUBMIT</Button>
<Button bg="red">SUBMIT</Button>
<Button bg="green">SUBMIT</Button>`} __scope={{props,Button}}>
  <Button >SUBMIT</Button>
   <Button bg='red'>SUBMIT</Button>
   <Button bg='green'>SUBMIT</Button>
</Playground>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"properties"}}>{`Properties`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`The below properties can be used to affect the appearance and behaviour of the component.`}</MDXTag>
<PropsTable of={Button} /></MDXTag>
